('<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: xx-large;">Welcome to OSU HVZ!<br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">The game begins 4/9/2010</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Registration deadline is 4/3/2010 by 5:00 pm</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Testing.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Trolling.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">herp derp was here</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong><u>Important Info:</u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">The game begins Friday, April 9th at 7:00am  and will run to Saturday, April 17th.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">There will be orientations for players to  come and get headbands, learn the rules, meet the mods and sign forms.  In order to participate, you must register an account and attend one  orientation session. There will be three orientations offered - Monday,  March 29th, Tuesday, March 30th, and Saturday, April 3rd.&nbsp; The exact  time of the orientations is still to be announced, because we don''t all  know what our spring term schedules will look like.&nbsp; <strong>The  registration deadline (as in the very very last chance) to register will  be at the Saturday orientation.</strong> Please register sooner rather  than later so we have a chance to make everyone''s headbands :)</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">All information will be given out by email, so please make sure you sign up with a valid one and chack often. If you have any questions or concerns, please (please please) contact   your moderators at <u><span><a class="smarterwiki-linkify" href="mailto:hvsz.osu@gmail.com">hvsz.osu@gmail.com</a></span></u></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong><u>About HVZ:</u></strong>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Humans vs Zombies is a game of a massive  scale. Designed to be anywhere from a single weekend to multi-week  spanning games, it is played (mainly) on college campuses, with some  games growing as large as 1000 people.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe basic structure of the game is a form of moderated tag. There has  been a Zombie breakout on campus. The two teams, the Humans, and the  Zombies, are represented by the players of the game. The Zombies'' goal  is to &quot;convert&quot; all humans before starving to death, and the Humans''  goal is to survive the zombie outbreak.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nZombies attack humans by tagging them, and must &quot;feed&quot; on a human within  a specific time, or they starve to death. Humans can defend themselves  by shooting the Zombies with Nerf toys or balled up socks, which stun  Zombies.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">HVZ began at OSU&nbsp;in Spring 2008 and was played in Wilson Hall. The following fall term 2009, OSU had it''s first week-long, campus game, with roughly 240 participants. It was a horde victory.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">This time around we hope to see our number increase, and have some awesome surprises in store for our players. Sound awesome to you? Then sign up!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Happy hunting!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img alt="" src="http://img214.imageshack.us/img214/1070/lolmm.png" /><strong><u><br />\r\n</u></strong></p>', '<p>\r\n<meta content="text/html; charset=utf-8" http-equiv="Content-Type">\r\n<meta content="Word.Document" name="ProgId">\r\n<meta content="Microsoft Word 12" name="Generator">\r\n<meta content="Microsoft Word 12" name="Originator">\r\n<link href="file:///C:\\Users\\BECKIZ~1\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\msohtmlclip1\\01\\clip_filelist.xml" rel="File-List" />\r\n<link href="file:///C:\\Users\\BEC